Quick Installation Instructions
-------------------------------

	The Cycon Odyssey is a game module for the Cog Engine Program. 
This release includes version 1.0 of the Cog Engine, which requires a Java 
environment to be executed. Fortunately, most modern browsers include the 
ability to view Java applets, although the current release of Microsoft's 
Internet Explorer includes a non-standard (and broken!) version of Java. 
The Netscape browser works much better with the Cog Engine.


The following Instructions work for all Operating Systems (Windows 98, 
Windows 2000, Windows XP, Linux, MacOS, etc.)


If you have a Netscape Browser:

1) Download the Cycon Odyssey zip file for the Cog Engine homepage:

http://cogengine.sourceforge.net/


2) Extract all of the files from the zip file. Be careful to maintain the 
file's directory structure (all images should end up in the "Images" 
subdirectory)


3) Load the "CogEngine.html" file into your Netscape web browser, or the
Java Appletviewer.


For Microsoft Internet Explorer 5 or 6:

1) Download and Install the Java Plug-In from Sun.com. The following page 
has the Download link for the Plug-In, as well as Installation 
Instructions:

http://java.sun.com/getjava/download.html

2) Download the Cycon Odyssey zip file for the Cog Engine homepage:

http://cogengine.sourceforge.net/


3) Extract all of the files from the zip file. Be careful to maintain the 
file's directory structure (all images should end up in the "Images" 
subdirectory)


4) Load the "CogEngine.html" file into your web browser, or the Java 
Appletviewer.



